e. The story of how evidence for the so-called ";Lambda-Cold Dark Matter"; model of cosmology has been gathered by generations of scientists throughout the world is told here by one of the pioneers of the field, Jeremiah Ostriker, and his coauthor Simon Mitton.From humankind's early attempts to comprehend Earth's place in the solar system, to astronomers' exploration of the Milky Way galaxy and the realm of the nebulae beyond, to the detection of the primordial fluctuations of energy from which all subsequent structure developed, this book explains the physics and the history of how the current model of our universe arose and has passed every test hurled at it by the skeptics. Throughout this rich story, an essential theme is emphasized: how three aspects of rational inquiry—the application of direct measurement and observation, the introduction of mathematical modeling, and the requirement that hypotheses should be testable and verifiable—guide scientific progress and underpin our modern cosmological paradigm.This monumental puzzle is far from complete, however, as scientists confront the mysteries of the ultimate causes of cosmic structure formation and the real nature and origin of dark matter and dark energy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSCIENCE / Astronomy.2bisacsh  aAge of the universe.  aAstronomer.  aAstronomical object.  aAstronomy.  aAstrophysics.  aAtomic nucleus.  aBackground radiation.  aBeatrice Tinsley.  aBig Bang.  aCalculation.  aCepheid variable.  aChemical element.  aChronology of the universe.  aCosmic background radiation.  aCosmic distance ladder.  aCosmic microwave background.  aCosmic ray.  aCosmological constant.  aDark energy.  aDeceleration parameter.  aDensity.  aEdwin Hubble.  aEinstein field equations.  aFritz Zwicky.  aGalaxy cluster. 